Current Learning Objectives:
Learn about virtual environments;
Use a task runner to manage environments and run code;
Create and install a Python package;
Create and run a test;
Learn about publishing a package on PyPI;
Learn about the basics of setting up tests;
Learn about the basics of setting up static checks;
Learn how to write reports in the form of a vignette, using R Markdown.

Understand what a package is; 
Understand why a package is useful;
Understand the tools used to create a package;
Install packages from other locations, such as GitHub;
Build, install and attach your own packages;
Learn how to add a license to a new R package;
Learn how to create a battery of basic tests;

For researchers wanting to adhere to FAIR practies.  Course provides code for exercises.
Introduce what FAIR means especially in relationship to code written for research purposes.
Course is comprehensive covering the research code lifecylce, describing good practices at each stage:
 Creating a github project (along with practices to help with version control); 
Practices to help with reproductibility (eg creating reproducible environment for other reseaerches, dependencies trees, VMs); 
Practices to annotate code to ensure that others can understand and use the code;
Code structure recommendations; Testing and Documentation practices

